text: Cheryl Rey (born August 1953 or 1954) is a Canadian former long track speed skater from Winnipeg, Manitoba, who was active in the late 1960s and early 1970s. Rey represented her nation at the World Allround Speed Skating Championships for Women in 1970, finishing 22nd overall and at the World Sprint Speed Skating Championships for Women in 1970, finishing 26th overall. She also competed at other international competitions in Austria and Germany. == Records== === Personal records === ==References== Category:1950s births Category:Canadian female speed skaters Category:Living people Category:Sportspeople from Winnipeg Category:Date of birth missing (living people)
